  correct_answer = 'A',
  explanation = 'Analogies are helpful to the reader because they make connections between unfamiliar concepts and concepts that the reader already understands. These connections can help the reader grasp the author’s argument more fully. The passage states that "The author of the book uses a variety of rhetorical devices to persuade the reader to agree with her argument. One of th…", which is the textual anchor for eliminating weaker choices. Choice A is correct because it aligns with that evidence: provide a deeper understanding of the author’s argument.. Each incorrect option either contradicts a explicit detail, imports information not present in the text, or answers a different question than the one asked.',
