  stimulus_text = 'In his book, *The Power of Myth*, Joseph Campbell argues that myths are not merely stories but also representations of deep, universal truths about the human experience. Campbell explains that myths are not simply about gods and monsters, but about the fundamental challenges and possibilities that all humans face. He suggests that myths can help us to understand our own lives and to find meaning in a world that can often feel chaotic and meaningless. Which of the following best summarizes Campbell’s main point in the excerpt?',
